On Sun, Feb 27, 2005 at 02:47:58PM -0800, Mark Hineline wrote:
> I've got some problems with lifters that aren't rock hard yet, and so 
> it's difficult to get a good valve adjustment. But it runs.

the lifters dont' have to be rock hard for adjustment. All you are
doing is to adjust the valves 1-2 (depending on preference) turns past
first contact. While they might compress while running until properly
pumped up it will not affect the adjustment.

